Quality Control
Several steps and checks will be carried out in order to maintain and ensure the quality of the A Team's What's Open Android application. Unit testing will occur at every step of the process, in addition to user testing once the product is complete. Progress reports will be filled out at the end of each week detailing what has been accomplished in that time as well. In addition, user feedback and ratings through the application and the Android Market, and analysis of anonymous statistics gathered by the application will be used. The Beta testing will consist of two phases. In the first phase, the A Team will be distributing the application to their friends and the people they know. These users will give feedback on the experience through surveys and in person. After a couple weeks, the feedback will be reviewed. Any changes or fixes will be made as necessary. The second stage will involve a stable, fully functional, Beta version of the application being released onto the Android Market.


Risk Management
We will be testing throughout the creation of the app. Aside from that, I’m not sure what risk there really is. 
Locations changing (any information) (have an email users can send a message to with updates)
Will students use it (marketing, flyers, and posters)
bugs in program (testing)
Team members dropping the class (division of work and equal knowledge so if one team member leaves, all we need to do is have the others work more)
People lying to us on questionnaires (give questionnaires out to many people)
